article.headline: Wichita St. 74, Iowa 57
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- Wichita State cruised to a 74-57 victory over Iowa on Tuesday in the consolation game of the CBE Classic behind 18 points from sophomore Garrett Stutz. The 7-foot Stutz scored 16 points in the first half on 7-of-8 shooting from the field. He scored 10 straight points during one stretch, hit his first two 3-pointers and made a steal during a 13-2 run that put Wichita State (2-2) in control. Toure' Murry also scored 18 for the Shockers. Iowa (1-4) never got closer than 7 points in the second half. The Hawkeyes got 18 points from Cully Payne.
